3 Months</div></div><div
class="how-to-desc"><div
class="how-to-image">
<picture>
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-hair-salon-guide-800x800-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Start a Hair Salon:">
</picture></div><p>The hair salon industry is favorable to small businesses. Less than 10% of the market is controlled by major companies. This means that entering this growing industry does not require a large investment. We've created a detailed guide to help you enter this growing market.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-what-type-of-hair-salon-you-want-to-open>Decide what type of hair salon you want to open.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-the-different-types-of-hair-salons>Research the different types of hair salons.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-the-different-types-of-hair-salons-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research the different types of hair salons."></div></div><p>There are five main types of hair salons: basic value-priced salon, boutique, salon and spa, specialty, and barbershop. Each type of hair salon offers a different range of services and attracts different customers.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Basic value-based hair salon:</strong> Basic value-based hair salons offer few services, focusing mostly on haircuts. These types of hair salons are usually franchises or chains, and they accept walk-in appointments. Their haircuts are reasonably priced and the stylists work quickly.</p></li><li><p><strong>Boutique hair salon:</strong> Boutique hair salons are a mix between a hair salon and a retail store. They offer the usual hair salon services, but also sell items such as books, jewelry, clothing, candles, etc. Boutique salons generally cater to women.</p></li><li><p><strong>Salon and spa:</strong> A salon and spa offer hair services along with full pampering experiences. They are often high-end and expensive, and some even have liquor licenses.</p></li><li><p><strong>Specialty hair salon:</strong> Specialty hair salons rely on specialist stylists to offer clients services that require advanced techniques. Often, these salons employ only a few stylists, each a master in one particular area.</p></li><li><p><strong>Barbershop:</strong> A barbershop mainly caters to men, offering simple cuts and styles, and various grooming services. The decor is mostly simple and most barbers are men.</p></li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=consider-your-expertise-and-qualifications>Consider your expertise and qualifications.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-consider-your-expertise-and-qualifications-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Consider your expertise and qualifications."></div></div><p>The type of hair salon you choose to open should complement the skills and qualifications you have to offer. For instance, a barber will have different techniques and cutting methods than a boutique hairstylist.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=create-a-business-plan>Create a business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=conduct-research-on-the-hair-salon-industry>Conduct research on the hair salon industry.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-conduct-research-on-the-hair-salon-industry-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Conduct research on the hair salon industry."></div></div><p>Market research is a great way to highlight your growth potential, identify your target market and competitors, compare pricing, and measure brand awareness. The process involves distributing surveys, gathering statistics, and creating reports.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=use-your-research-to-compile-a-detailed-business-plan>Use your research to compile a detailed business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-use-research-to-create-a-detailed-business-plan-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Use your research to compile a detailed business plan."></div></div><p>A business plan should describe your hair salon business and brand, show how your business will grow, define what it will need to succeed, and outline possible challenges your business is likely to face. This business plan is a sort of road map for you in the early stages, and it can be used to get financing and attract partners.</p><p><strong>Essentials for a hair salon business plan:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Executive Summary.</p></li><li><p>Industry Overview.</p></li><li><p>Market Analysis.</p></li><li><p>Sales and Marketing Plan.</p></li><li><p>Ownership and Management Plan.</p></li><li><p>Operating Plan.</p></li><li><p>Financial Plan.</p></li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Check out our generic business plan template for a hair salon. <strong>Download link listed above</strong>.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-your-hair-salon>Form your hair salon.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-legal-structure>Choose a legal structure.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-business-structures-288x288-20200820.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a legal structure."></div></div><p>Forming a business entity protects you from liability and can save you money on taxes. You have four possible legal structures to choose from for your hair salon: sole proprietorship, partnership, limited liability company, and corporation.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Most salon owners choose LLC.</strong> This structure protects you from personal liability if there is an unfortunate slip of the scissors. LLC's are more flexible when it comes to taxes, but can be difficult to set up.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Once you've chosen your legal structure, file a DBA (Doing business as), or file LLC paperwork with the State.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-business-name>Choose a business name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-business-name-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a business name."></div></div><p>You want the name of your hair salon to be catchy and unique, while cleverly hinting to the services you provide. However, naming your business can be a time-consuming process as there are many steps to follow. Check out our detailed guide on <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/guides/how-to-name-your-hair-salon">how to name your hair salon</a>.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=open-a-business-bank-account>Open a business bank account.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-bank-account-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Open a business bank account."></div></div><p>Opening a business bank account that is separate from your personal accounts protects you from liability and gains you access to business banking services. Visit your local financial institutions and ask them about their business accounts.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>To help you better manage your finances, you may also want to establish an accounting system.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-business-insurance>Get business insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-business-insurance-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get business insurance."></div></div><p>To protect your business from losses caused by lawsuits, fire, flood, theft etc., you need business insurance. These may include liability insurance, commercial property insurance, and more.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=invest-in-hair-salon-software>Invest in hair salon software.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-invest-in-salon-software-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Invest in hair salon software."></div></div><p>Salon management software will help you to schedule and manage appointments, process sales and payments, and manage client information. Popular options include Salonist, Shedul, and Versum.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-hair-salon-section3-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-location>Choose a location.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-location-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a location."></div></div><p>This is one of the most important decisions you'll make when starting your salon. Depending on your budget, you may decide to set up your salon in the city center, or on the outskirts of town, near tourist attractions, or in a new mall. It is all up to you, but there are many things to consider before leasing commercial property.</p><p><strong>Think about the following factors when making your choice:</strong></p><ul><li>Is the location close to your target market?</li><li>Is there public transport nearby?</li><li>Does the space offer ample room for at least three stylists and an admin clerk?</li><li>Is the location safe?</li><li>Are there amenities available?</li></ul><div
class="step-direction tip">
